You can build an RPM package of insilicoPlatform by just running make(1)
in this directory.

== Requirements

Make sure that rpmbuild(8) is installed on your system, and follow the
instruction at:
https://wiki.centos.org/HowTos/SetupRpmBuildEnvironment
git(1) is also required to create archive of Flint's source code.


== Configuration

Create config.mk in order to specify DIST and GTK_PACKAGE_NAME.
See config.mk.el7 or config.mk.el8 for example boilerplate.


== Reference

For more information about creating rpm packages:
https://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/quick-docs/creating-rpm-packages/
